criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Adults ≥ 18 years old, both genres, who consent to participate of the study

          -  Patients who were diagnosed with SJ according to the criteria of the American College
             of Rheumatology and the European League against Rheumatism

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients who have undergone head and neck radiation therapy;

          -  Patients with a history of neoplasias and salivary gland infections;

          -  Patients with acquired immunodeficiency virus infection, sarcoidosis, viral hepatitis,
             diabetes mellitus and smokers;

          -  Patients with inability to undergo total saliva collection by established techniques;

          -  Patients who can not attend regular acupuncture sessions;

          -  Patients who had a change in the dosage of medications in use within 6 weeks before
             the start of the study.

          -  Patients who received acupuncture therapy up to 6 weeks prior to the start of the
             study.
